
Credentials are needed to gain access to information or resources.

A classical example of credentials is the combination of username and → development/security/password.
-
Other types of credential providing include
  • biometrics (such as fingerprints, voice recognition and retinal scans)
  • → development/security/cryptography/X_509
  • → development/security/cryptography/Public-key-certificate[public key certificates]
  • …

sa:
  → development/web/RFC#rfc-7617[RFC-7617] defines the `Basic` → development/web/HTTP authentication scheme which transmits *credentials* as user-id/password pairs, encoded using → development/Base64.

  The → Windows/security/credential-manager[Windows Credential Manager].

  The → Windows/PowerShell command noun → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/credential[`credential`] and the → Microsoft/dot-net class
  → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Management/Automation/PSCredential[`System.Management.Automation.PSCredential`].
